extends is a Java keyword.Used in class and interface definition to declare the class or interface that is to be extended.Syntax:public class MyClass extends SuperClass 
{
  //...
}

public interface MyInterface extends SuperInterface
{
  //...
}In Java 1.5 and later, the "extends" keyword is also used to specify an upper bound on a type parameter in Generics.class Foo<T extends Number> { /*...*/ }See also:Java Programming/Creating Objects
